text: it's nice to see how involved ten was in the creative process. he knows all the references, the meaning of every detail and how it enters into the story at large, and had discussions with the staff to realize his own vision. that's such a contrast to how idols usually only have a vague idea of what's going on. even when you hear about soloist being "involved", ie contributing some lyrics or choreo, i often feel like that's just to add a glaze of authenticity (bcs that's the fashion nowadays), but their actual influence is usually much more restricted. i mean they have busy schedules after all. so i'm pleasently surprised at how much creative controll ten had.
